Manchester City recorded away wins against Sunderland, Leicester and West Brom and beat Everton and Crystal Palace at the Etihad.

The only blot on Pellegrini's copybook was a 2-2 home draw with relegation candidates Burnley after City threw away a two-goal lead in the final game of the year.

That run of form is even more impressive considering Pellegrini had to deal with a spate of injuries that decimated his forward line, including an injury to star striker Sergio Aguero at the start of the month. 

